        "section_id": "dha-rhinosinusitis-i2-history",
        "heading": "5. Types; 8. Clinical History",
        "locator": "pages 8 and 12–14",
        "evidence_summary": "Defines duration patterns and lists congestion, discharge, postnasal drip, dental discomfort, facial pain or pressure, fever, fatigue, cough, smell change, and headache."
      },
      {
        "section_id": "dha-rhinosinusitis-i2-red-flags",
        "heading": "9. Red Flags",
        "locator": "pages 14–15",
        "evidence_summary": "Lists high fever, frontal or periorbital swelling, severe headache, meningeal or mental-status change, visual change, and persistent unilateral or bloody symptoms."
      },
      {
        "section_id": "dha-rhinosinusitis-i2-investigations-referral",
        "heading": "12. Investigations; 13. Referral Criteria",
        "locator": "pages 17–19",
        "evidence_summary": "Limits imaging and other tests to clinician-selected contexts and lists emergency, specialist, systemic-illness, and non-response referral criteria."
      },
      {
        "section_id": "dha-rhinosinusitis-i2-management",
        "heading": "14. Management",
        "locator": "pages 19–24",
        "evidence_summary": "Provides clinician-led conservative and pharmacological management choices; no dose-bearing content is mapped into this project."
      }
    ],
